# text label to numeric
encoder = LabelEncoder()

sp['gender'] = encoder.fit_transform(sp['gender'])
gender_mapping = {index : label for index , label in enumerate(encoder.classes_)}


sp['race/ethnicity'] = encoder.fit_transform(sp['race/ethnicity'])
ethnicity_mapping = {index : label for index , label in enumerate(encoder.classes_)}

sp['parental level of education'] = encoder.fit_transform(sp['parental level of education'])
parent_education_mapping = {index : label for index , label in enumerate(encoder.classes_)}

sp['lunch'] = encoder.fit_transform(sp['lunch'])
lunch_mapping = {index : label for index , label in enumerate(encoder.classes_)}

sp['test preparation course'] = encoder.fit_transform(sp['test preparation course'])
test_prep_mapping = {index : label for index , label in enumerate(encoder.classes_)}

from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
wcss=[]
for i in range (1,11):
 kmeans=KMeans(n_clusters=i,init='k-means++',random_state=42)
 kmeans.fit(scaled_features_sp)
 wcss.append(kmeans.inertia_)
plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
plt.plot(range(1,11), wcss, 'bx-')
plt.title('The Elbow Method')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
plt.show()
In [42]:
# Silhouette Score
from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score
silhouette_scores = []
for i in range(2,10):
    m1=KMeans(n_clusters=i, random_state=42)
    c = m1.fit_predict(scaled_features_sp)
    silhouette_scores.append(silhouette_score(scaled_features_sp, m1.fit_predict(scaled_features_sp))) 
plt.bar(range(2,10), silhouette_scores) 
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters', fontsize = 20) 
plt.ylabel('S(i)', fontsize = 20) 
plt.show()
In [43]:
sc=max(silhouette_scores)
number_of_clusters=silhouette_scores.index(sc)+2
print("Number of Cluster Required is : ", number_of_clusters)

Number of Cluster Required is :  2
In [44]:
# Clustering
# Training a predicting using K-Means Algorithm.
kmeans= KMeans(n_clusters= number_of_clusters, random_state= 42).fit(scaled_features_sp)
pred= kmeans.predict(scaled_features_sp)
# Appending those cluster value into main dataframe (without standard-scalar)
sp['cluster']= pred + 1

sns.set(rc={'axes.facecolor':'black', 'figure.facecolor':'black', 'axes.grid' : False, 'font.family': 'Dejavu Sans'})
for i in sp:
    diag = sns.FacetGrid(sp, col = "cluster", hue = "cluster", palette = "Set1")
    diag.map(plt.hist, i, bins=6, ec="k") 
    diag.set_xticklabels(rotation=25, color = 'white')
    diag.set_yticklabels(color = 'white')
    diag.set_xlabels(size=16, color = 'white')
    diag.set_titles(size=16, color = '#f01132', fontweight="bold")
    diag.fig.set_figheight(6)

Higher score student belong to cluster one.

Lower score Student belong to cluster two.

Gender: Females were more common in higher score students.

Race: Race groups C, D, and E were more common among higher score student.

Parent Education: Parent education of higher score Student are higher.

Lunch: Higher score students have more lunch.

Test Preparation: Completing test preparation course increase probability to have higher score.

#k-value using elbow method
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
distortions = []
K = range(1,10)
for k in K:
    kmeanModel = KMeans(n_clusters=k)
    kmeanModel.fit(sp)
    distortions.append(kmeanModel.inertia_)
plt.figure(figsize=(16,8))
plt.plot(K, distortions, 'bx-')
plt.xlabel('k')
plt.ylabel('Distortion')
plt.title('The Elbow Method showing the optimal k')
plt.show()
